--- !u!114 &808330728
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 808330726}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 202caef7457eee34c890dd81a29f5d0f, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  textDisplay: {fileID: 1204397614}
  normalCharDelay: 0.01
  fastCharDelay: 0.005
  test: "Cinder was a quiet young man reduced to servitude in his own home after
    his father\u2019s death. His stepmother and stepbrothers treated him as little
    more than ash and labor, while they prepared for the royal ball where the heir,
    Prince Elara, would choose a partner.\n\nLeft behind, Cinder wished only to be
    seen once as himself. A mysterious spirit answered, transforming his rags into
    elegant attire and sending him to the palace with a warning that the magic would
    end at midnight.\n\nAt the ball, Cinder moved with quiet grace, drawing Elara\u2019s
    attention not through status, but sincerity. For a fleeting moment, he belonged
    among silk and light. As midnight struck, he fled in fear, leaving behind a single
    glass slipper.\n\nThe kingdom searched for the one who fit it. When the guards
    arrived at his home, Cinder stepped forward, caught between hope and fear, knowing
    that being seen could either free him or bind him further."
